article.description: Grace Gantt scored 15 points off the bench to lead TCU to the upset win over Michigan State.
article.headline: TCU wins, but faces UConn next
article.linkText: TCU holds off Michigan State in East opener
article.story:
STORRS, Conn. (AP) -- Grace Gantt scored seven of her 15 points
in the final eight minutes as Texas Christian held off Michigan
State 50-47 in the first round of the East Regional on Sunday.

	   The ninth-seeded Horned Frogs (20-13) play No. 1 seed
Connecticut in the second round Tuesday night. The Huskies (32-1)
advanced earlier with a 91-44 win over Boston University.

	   The Spartans (17-12) rallied from a 16-point deficit in the
second half.

	   Syretta Bromfield led the Spartans with 18 points and 15
rebounds. She hit a 3-pointer with 44 seconds, cutting TCU's lead
to 45-41. Her layup with 3 seconds remaining pulled the Spartans to
48-47.

	   TCU's Ebony Shaw then iced the game, fielding the inbounds pass
at midcourt and racing untouched for a layup as time ran out.

	   Both teams struggled from the floor. Michigan State shot just 26
percent (17-of-64). TCU, which won the Conference USA tournament,
shot 32 percent (17-of-53).
